author: SONIA PÉREZ D. Associated Press
title: Guatemala: US deportations driving up COVID-19 cases
description: Guatemala's health minister says that deportees from the United States were helping drive up the country's COVID-19 caseload, adding that on one flight some 75% of the deportees tested positive for the virus
content:
GUATEMALA CITY -- 
Guatemala's health minister said Tuesday that deportees from the United States were driving up the country's COVID-19 caseload, adding that on one flight some 75% of the deportees tested positive for the virus.
